reason.tex:
%text We have to determine when $f'(x)$ is $>0$ and when it is $<0$, where \[ \qquad f'(x) = 12x\cdot (x+1)\cdot (x-2) \] There are three terms, $x, x+1$ and $x-2$, that will determine the sign of $f'(x)$ % \begin{align} \begin{tabular}{NNNNN}
\hline & x <-1 & (-1,0) & (0,2) & > 2 \\ \hline x & - & - & + & + \\ \hline x+1 & - & + & + & + \\ \hline x-2 & - & - & - & + \\ \hline f'(x) & - & + & - & + \\ \hline \end{tabular} \end{align} %text Which is why % \begin{align} \begin{tabular}{lN}
\hline & \text{Condition} \\ \hline \text{Strictly increasing} & x\in (-1,0)\cup (2,\infty) \\ \hline \text{Strictly decreasing} & x\in (-\infty,-1)\cup (0,2) \\ \hline \end{tabular} \end{align} %text %
